text:
40th Road, west from the N.W. corner of Main Street, showing thereon the John Titus Van de Water grocery store from 1865 to 1874, when Donley Brothers purchased it. They operated until 1877, then being financially embarassed, Divine Hewlett Van de Water took it over (1883). A Van de Water still owned it in 1897.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

Main Street (tracks thereon), at the S.W. corner of 40th Road, showing the former Halleran house (No. 113 Main Street, a hotel). J. J. Halleran, 1873; and John J. Halleran and Sons, 1898, were the owners. This building has been stuccoed and altered into stores.

1922.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

40th Road, north side, just west of Main Street, showing the fire house of Hook and Ladder 129. It is opposite the Flushing Railroad station.

P. L. Sperr
April 8, 1927

Main Street, east side, north from 40th Road, showing Flushing's main business street. Fairchild's Flushing Institute stood here in 1873 and 1891. View 2 is north from Roosevelt Avenue.

P. L. Sperr

August 21, 1935
Views 1,2
